---
name: webauthn-server-verify
backends: [int, js]
---

# WebAuthn server verifier — challenge issuance + garbage rejection match on INT and JS.

The interpreter uses the auth plugin (`scalascript.server.WebAuthn`); the JS backend uses the
standalone Node port (`JsRuntimeWebAuthn`). Both must mint a non-empty challenge and return
`None` for malformed registration/assertion input. (A full valid ceremony needs a real
authenticator and is exercised by busi's device tests.)

[webauthnChallenge, webauthnVerifyRegistration, webauthnVerifyAssertion](std/auth.ssc)

```scalascript
println(webauthnChallenge("owner").length > 10)
println(webauthnVerifyRegistration("e30", "o2NmbXQ", "https://busi.example") match { case None => "reg-none"; case _ => "reg-some" })
println(webauthnVerifyAssertion("e30", "AAAA", "MEUC", "cid", "https://busi.example") match { case None => "asr-none"; case _ => "asr-some" })
```
